input: had to go back & forth with customer service to get the same price two of my friends were paying... even tho i'm unemployed bc of covid & both of my friends have good jobs... first counselor i was paired with was a christian counselor (i'm jewish)... 2nd counselor was alright for a a week but then after a few weeks i realized all she ever did was ask me how i was doing every 2 days... the conversation never really went farther than that... the one time i opened up to that therapist she told me i had a choice in a particular situation where i really didn't, then she went onto brag about how she was homeless at 16 with 3 dependents... lol this counselor, according to betterhelp, supposedly had 25 years of experience & was competing with me about how bad our experiences were... so after that i switched a bunch of times bc i kept getting paired men or ppl with only a few years of experience... i know i'm a tough case... i know i need someone who can handle a lot... anyway, after the 5th or 6th switch i got frustrated over multiple misunderstandings with customer service about pricing so i asked for my money back & without any response or confirmation my subscription was cancelled 2 days later... after i had just turned in my first therapy assignment... and then i was told i wouldn't be able to get the same price i was paying before if i resigned up... so i responded by reminding them that they were in the business of helping ppl who are hurting & that their system was infuriating for someone who's just trying to get help... so then they changed their tune real quick & offered me the price i wanted but i told them i had already signed up with talkspace & immediately my experience was much better with zero frustrations!

input:
i accidentally downloaded it(via my niece) and now i got an update saying i am now a proud owner of the yearly subscription... this app does not make you calm i am highly irritated that they use marketing to little kids to get their sales.. she claimed she accidentally clicked and installed the app while watching ryan, she's only 3 going on 4 so i do not entirely blame her(although i have strictly told her not to download things from the ads she sees for these reasons) but i do understand the terms and services of apple and how they don't let you make returns on stuff like this, it's highly irritating and ironic that an app called calm would make me so dang agitated... please do not have a mindset of a 3 year old when downloading this or you'll pay the price of $75 as i have... 

merry christmas/ happy holidays :)) 

(i've copied and pasted into my notes incase this review is removed for any reason on distributers or apple's side)

input:
i've been using betterhelp for maybe six months now i have a student discount but even with the student discount it is pricey but i believe it is worth it you can switch your therapist if you don't like them which i do like a lot you can video chat text or phone call your therapist and share journal entries which i love you can also attend virtual meetings about other topics that you're interested in like group therapy
i went through two other therapist but i finally found the perfect one the other ones are really good though just not for me what issue i do have is that when i'm doing a voice call session if i hit mute and unmute then it keeps going back on mute every five seconds which is pretty annoying i've already reported it hopefully they can fix that bug soon but other than that the app functionality is good

the same two ppl narrate pretty much everything i tried on the app and the woman tamara's voice is extremely annoying 
i can't meditate to that 
i tried to get a refund and there's no way to contact anyone so think twice before you spend 65 dollars to try something because you can not get refund 
i will be calling credit card company tomorrow to do a charge back 
i used the app for about 30 minutes so i think a month charge would be fair but nope it's $65 .

input: even though mediation sounds dumb' for some people, headspace is the very opposite; it gives me mindfulness tips and follow up with a mediation, making the mindfulness lesson more memorable, and what i learned so far (and all of them are so freaking helpful) are: observe thoughts instead of reacting and getting carried away with them, if we're reacting to thoughts we are keeping the emotion alive, adding more fuel to the fire; let's thoughts come and go, with a gentle or effortless focus; having a daydream sense of mind let's us take things less seriously and it gives us more freedom, and sooooo many more (i can't remember all at the moment).
